        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <details>
            <summary>What is the best S&P 500 index fund for 2025?</summary>
            <p>The best fund depends on your brokerage and whether you prefer an ETF or a mutual fund. VOO and FXAIX are popular choices due to their extraordinarily low expense ratios and deep liquidity, making them ideal core holdings.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>Are S&P 500 index funds safe?</summary>
            <p>They offer broad market diversification, which mitigates individual stock risk, though they are still subject to overall market volatility. Historically, they represent one of the safest and most reliable ways to compound wealth over decades.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>How much should I invest in an S&P 500 fund?</summary>
            <p>Many financial advisors recommend making a broad market index fund the core of your portfolio, often 50-80% depending on age, risk tolerance, and individual financial goals.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>What is the average return of the S&P 500?</summary>
            <p>Historically, the S&P 500 has returned an average of about 10% per year before inflation, though this can vary wildly from year to year depending on macroeconomic conditions.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>Can I lose money in an S&P 500 index fund?</summary>
            <p>Yes, in the short term, market downturns and recessions will negatively affect the fund's value. However, historically the index has always recovered and reached new highs over longer time horizons.</p>
        </details>

